# GOLDEN trace fixture — emulator-gb (DMG LR35902)
# ============================================================================
# A minimal CORRECT per-instruction trace in gameboy-doctor format. The
# emulator-gb trace-diff gate compares an implementation's emitted trace line
# for line against a known-correct reference. This golden is that reference for
# a tiny hand-traced program; the gate MUST PASS it. If the gate rejects this
# golden it is over-strict (false-red) and is itself broken.
#
# Format (one line per instruction, BEFORE it executes); each NN is one hex byte,
# each NNNN a 16-bit hex word:
#   A:NN F:NN B:NN C:NN D:NN E:NN H:NN L:NN SP:NNNN PC:NNNN PCMEM:b0,b1,b2,b3
# F low nibble is ALWAYS 0 (INVARIANTS: mask F &= 0xF0). PCMEM = the 4 bytes at PC.
#
# Program traced (loaded at 0x0100), exercising flag-sensitive ops the mutants attack:
#   0100  3C        INC A         ; A 01->02, Z=0 N=0 H=0, C preserved (=1 from boot F=B0)
#   0101  3D        DEC A         ; A 02->01, Z=0 N=1 H=0, C preserved (=1)
#   0102  A7        AND A         ; A&A=01, Z=0 N=0 H=1 C=0  (AND forces H=1,C=0)
#   0103  18 02     JR  +2        ; signed e=+2; next PC = 0103+2(len)+2 = 0107
#   0107  00        NOP
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Post-boot register init (INVARIANTS): A=01 F=B0 B=00 C=13 D=00 E=D8 H=01 L=4D SP=FFFE PC=0100
A:01 F:B0 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0100 PCMEM:3C,3D,A7,18
A:02 F:10 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0101 PCMEM:3D,A7,18,02
A:01 F:50 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0102 PCMEM:A7,18,02,00
A:01 F:10 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0103 PCMEM:18,02,00,00
A:01 F:10 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0107 PCMEM:00,00,00,00
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Line-by-line flag derivation (the gate diffs each field; these are the truths):
#  L1 PC=0100 INC A : entry A=01 F=B0(Z1 N0 H1 C1). next line shows the RESULT state.
#  L2 PC=0101 (after INC A): A=02. Z=0 (2!=0), N=0, H=0 (low nibble 1->2, no carry),
#             C PRESERVED =1 (INVARIANTS: INC r leaves C). F = Z0 N0 H0 C1 = 0x10.
#  L3 PC=0102 (after DEC A): A=01. Z=0, N=1, H=0 (low nibble 2->1, was not 0 so H=0),
#             C PRESERVED =1. F = Z0 N1 H0 C1 = 0x50.
#  L4 PC=0103 (after AND A): A=01&01=01. AND rule: Z=0 N=0 H=1 C=0. F = 0x10.
#  L5 PC=0107 (after JR +2): JR affects NO flags -> F stays 0x10. PC = 0103 + 2 + (+2) = 0107.
# Every F value has low nibble 0 (masked). This is the falsifiability surface the
# mutants force-h-zero, skip-f-mask, and jr-off-by-one each break in exactly one place.
